  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Digital and tech skills training for refugee and Greek youth</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing opportunities to a group currently out of the humanitarian response support for acquiring valuable professional skills
Fostering learning and exchange among a mixed group of youth, thus supporting the early integration efforts currently needed in Greece</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a 2-month pilot project over May and June 2017.
The project aims to test the delivery of digital and tech skills training to a group of young refugees and Greeks within a youth centre in Athens.
The objective is as much to test the vocational training aspect - covering a gap in opportunities offered to refugees over 15 years old - as to provide a common space for refugees and Greeks to interact and learn together - fostering integration and exchanges between those groups.</narrative>
  </description>
